content:
Note Title: It's only April, everything is still on track!
    Note Content: #I will be moved by words [topic]#
Having chosen to take the postgraduate entrance exam, only I know how challenging this journey has been. The life of postgraduate candidates is like a phoenix being reborn in fire, so I tell myself I must succeed! Later, I followed the teacher's instructions completely, including each mock test, which boosted my confidence. Back when I imagined my life after the exam, it was always with a smile (truly). Although the preliminary exam score is 180+, it does not mean success. The re-examination is still full of challenges. Take each day one step at a time.
As for the preliminary exam, I feel that during the rigorous days and nights of preparation, the main takeaway is the tempering of one's willpower. I no longer care about others' opinions; their perspectives and suggestions can be referenced, but they should not influence my goals. Some people shout about positivity every day yet live in a muddled way. Those who are truly prepared don't need motivational encouragement because they spend their time downloading past papers and searching for materials. People who feel empty inside often look for motivational quotes for comfort. Only by taking real action can one feel fulfilled and steadfast. Success is achieved step by step‚Äîthis is my advice to junior students.

content:
Note Title: Understand Him to Better Comprehend His Works
    Note Content: When I opened this book, I was greatly surprised to find that the preface alone was 70 pages long. After patiently reading it, I gained a deeper understanding of Yasunari Kawabata's experiences and works. Sometimes, when reading a book, we seek some moral lessons from it. However, in Yasunari Kawabata's writings, I find no such lessons. What I see instead is a faint sense of aesthetic beauty and sorrow. Perhaps this is the literary beauty he pursued.
	
He said, whether it‚Äôs ‚ÄúThe Dancing Girl of Izu‚Äù or ‚ÄúSnow Country,‚Äù I wrote them with a sense of gratitude for love. These works are inseparable from his tragic experiences.
	
Orphaned at an early age, he lived with his grandparents. At the age of seven, his grandmother passed away, leaving him to live with his deaf and blind grandfather, leading a desolate and lonely life. One can imagine how solitary, bleak, and dreary their lives must have been. At sixteen, his grandfather also passed away. At an age when he still needed care and affection, he prematurely experienced life's impermanence, which predestined the unique sorrow of his life.
	
He himself once described himself as a "drifting orphan." The desolation and pain of life and death during his childhood deeply permeated his emotions and spirit. Later, he lived with his uncle‚Äôs family. He became increasingly withdrawn, feeling like an unneeded ‚Äúextra person.‚Äù Yet, deep inside, he intensely yearned for human warmth, friendship, and love. Fortunately, the change in his educational environment helped him open his heart. He was admitted to Tokyo Imperial University‚Äôs English Department, where he made many new friends.
	
A year later, he grew tired of the boarding school life and decided to travel alone to the Izu Peninsula. This eventually resulted in the creation of his beautifully realistic literary masterpiece, ‚ÄúThe Dancing Girl of Izu.‚Äù
	
A disheartened young man encounters a group of traveling entertainers during his journey and decides to travel with them. Their kind hearts gave him an unprecedented sense of warmth, especially the innocent dancing girl whose affection opened up his heart. He seemed to see a beam of light piercing through the long-standing haze in his heart, instantly dispelling his frustration.
	
These subtle romantic feelings made the journey more enchanting, perhaps reflecting the unique charm of Japanese aesthetics. However, people on different paths must part eventually. The sorrow of farewell is also faint but lingers, leaving a lasting impact.
	
Reading this book and watching ‚ÄúThe Dancing Girl of Izu‚Äù starring Momoe Yamaguchi and Tomokazu Miura create a vivid cinematic experience.
	
This book includes 11 poetic novels by Yasunari Kawabata, such as ‚ÄúThe Dancing Girl of Izu‚Äù and ‚ÄúA Story of Bones.‚Äù Reading it on a rainy day brings an extraordinary feeling. #BookSharing[Topic]# #GoodBooks[Topic]# #JisiEducationBookClub[Topic]# #NotebookInspiration[Topic]#

Note Title: Lightning Protection Guide for Getting Bracelets at the Yonghe Temple
    Note Content: ‚ÄºÔ∏èIf you don't have the determination to wake up at six and the perseverance to queue for two hours, don't even bother going. I arrived after the doors opened and still ended up queuing for two hours [crying R][crying R]
	
‚ùóÔ∏èYonghe Temple opens at 9 AM on weekdays and 8:30 AM on weekends. This time I went late [crying R][crying R]
	
‚ùóÔ∏èThere are no incense ash porcelain and incense ash glass on weekends and the first and fifteenth days of the lunar month, see photo 7, but there are incense ash half-sugar and incense ash snowball, see photo 1
	
‚û°Ô∏èPersonally, I think it will be very crowded at any of the Dharma item distribution areas (but if you really arrive very early, ignore what I said). I queued at the second one (the largest one), and by the time I got there, the line had reached the small forest behind the main gate. If you see a long line there, don't hesitate and wait there
‚û°Ô∏èLooking up styles online really speeds things up. Just show the picture to the cashier and ask if they have it. If they do, just proceed. You can look at several styles in case the one you choose is not available, then ask for another one. Otherwise, you'll have to squeeze at the counter with others, which is really difficult
‚û°Ô∏èThe third Dharma item distribution area is next to the consecration room, the smallest one, and it seems not many people, but the queue should also be slow
‚û°Ô∏èThe consecration process is indeed fast, with a batch of people entering at a time, but you still need to queue as many people want to have their items consecrated
‚ùï‚ùïSmall tips: You can bring a power bank, a bottle of water, and if it's sunny, remember to bring sunglasses and a hat. If you have the energy, bring a small stool as well.

content:
Note Title: Renovation Process | Comprehensive Sharing of Tips (Directly Copy My Work)
    Note Content: Hello, I am KakalaÔΩû
I didn't hire a renovation company or designer, and successfully saved a significant amount of money (at least 30,000-50,000 yuan).
Because I prepared a lot before the renovation, looked at various materials,
I gained a general understanding framework of the renovation process.
Ô∏è1. First, you need to understand renovation materials, construction techniques, and market prices (if unsure, visit local renovation markets where you can get detailed introductions to establish a basic understanding of renovation).
2. The key is to decide on a style you like for your renovation. If unsure, look at samples online.
If you're really unclear, you can take a little test on platforms like Zhuxiao~bang to help choose a style you like. It's quite convenient.
Once you've decided on a style, collect more reference pictures. Don't easily change the overall direction of style after it's set; otherwise, it's easy to end up with a mismatched look.
Ô∏è3. You can also check out information on inspection during the handover of your property. Be very thorough, and if there are any issues, have the property management repair them.
Ô∏è4. Order central air conditioning/duct systems, windows, floor heating, and cabinets in advance. Before construction starts, have the cabinet designer measure the kitchen's dimensions and provide a water and electricity layout plan.
Ô∏è5. Set a date to begin construction and coordinate the entire renovation layout. Give the kitchen water and electricity layout plan to the workers, and coordinate the full-house water and electricity setup, along with purchasing materials.
6. Start demolition and restructuring, such as stripping old walls.
Ô∏èÔ∏è7. Begin water and electricity setup, with the central air conditioning/duct system and floor heating technicians entering the site simultaneously to communicate with the electricians and plumbers. (Communication between trades is very important.)
8. Initial inspection of water and electricity work. Check if switches, outlets, pipes, and wires are properly installed, and if anything is missing or misplaced.
Ô∏èÔ∏è9. Fill channels and level kitchen/bathroom floors. Apply waterproofing (install squat toilets).
Ô∏èÔ∏è10. Seal balconies and install windows.
11. Install central air conditioning/duct systems and lay floor heating.
Ô∏èÔ∏è12. Have the water pipe manufacturer conduct a pressure test, take photos for records, and issue a test report.
Ô∏èÔ∏è13. Brief the masons, purchase materials, and let the masons start their work.
Ô∏èÔ∏è14. After the masons finish, re-measure for cabinets, take initial measurements for customized furniture, and wait two days before applying floor protection.
Ô∏èÔ∏è15. Brief the carpenters, purchase materials, and start carpentry work (including ceiling installations and curtain box reservations).
Ô∏èÔ∏è16. After carpentry is complete, re-measure for customized furniture.
Ô∏èÔ∏è17. Brief the painters, purchase materials, and start painting work.
Ô∏èÔ∏è18. Install cabinets and integrated ceilings.
Ô∏èÔ∏è19. Before putty sanding, install wardrobe cabinets; before the second layer of putty, paste gypsum lines.
Ô∏èÔ∏è20. After putty, clean all house dust, then apply one layer of primer and two layers of topcoat. Wait two days before entering or opening windows.
‚úÖ Water, electricity, masonry, carpentry, and painting completedüîö. Hard renovation ends, entering the installation phase:
Ô∏èÔ∏è1. Install wooden doors and door frames.
Ô∏èÔ∏è2. Apply grout (do not enter the house within three days of grouting).
Ô∏èÔ∏è3. Install and debug the central air conditioning/duct system return air outlets.
Ô∏èÔ∏è4. Install sanitary ware and hardware appliances.
5. Install kitchen and bathroom doors.
Ô∏èÔ∏è6. Install switches, outlets, and lighting.
Ô∏èÔ∏è7. Conduct initial cleaning.
Ô∏èÔ∏è8. Bring in furniture, appliances, and decorations.
9. Schedule gas activation.

content:
Note Title: How to recover files deleted from USB drive
    Note Content: When we need to store data files, we choose some storage tools like cloud drives or USB drives according to our actual needs to complete the storage work. However, accidents are inevitable during use. For example, when we use a USB drive, files may be lost or deleted due to various reasons. How can we recover files deleted from a USB drive in such cases? After reading this article, you will be able to quickly recover deleted files.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄSince USB drives are used on various computers, they are prone to virus infections. These viruses may add useless files that occupy space in the USB drive or disguise file names and icons as regular files. When users insert the USB drive, these malicious programs may automatically run, delete files, or modify file attributes.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄOf course, mistakes on our part can also lead to files being accidentally deleted, such as unintentionally pressing the Delete key on the keyboard or deletion during USB drive cleanup by a cleaning tool.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄSo how can we recover files deleted from a USB drive?

First, check if there is a backup. This can prevent file loss due to accidental deletion. If you have backed up the files before using the USB drive, you can restore the deleted files by copying the backup files back to the USB drive. Alternatively, you can recover them from their original saved location, such as on a computer or other storage device.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄIf the above methods do not allow you to recover the deleted files or if no backup was made, you can consider downloading professional data recovery software. This software scans the disk where you need to recover data and helps retrieve the files you want to recover. Below, I will use the EaseUS Data Recovery Wizard as an example to demonstrate the specific operations:

Step 1: Connect the USB drive to the computer. Note: After connecting the USB drive, refrain from performing any new read or write operations on it to avoid further data damage.

Step 2: Based on the disk displayed on the computer for the USB drive (for example, select ‚ÄúLocal Disk (E:\)‚Äù function), click ‚ÄúNext‚Äù to proceed. Step 3: In the scan mode selection, choose accidental deletion scan and click ‚ÄúNext,‚Äù or select the deep scan function. Step 4: Select the file type you need to recover. After selection, click ‚ÄúScan.‚Äù Step 5: Once the scan is complete, there will be a lot of data. Find the important files you believe need recovery, preview them to ensure they can be restored. After confirming the files to recover, check them, and click the recover button below to save the recovered files to a designated location.

content:
Note Title: These 5 Bad Skincare Habits, See How Many You've Fallen For
    Note Content:	


Popular skincare products recommended online don't seem to work well for you, and there are so many trendy skincare methods that it's dizzying. How much of it is true and how much is false? Today, XXX will talk about several bad skincare habits that are easy to fall into. Avoiding them can help you achieve good skin~

¬†

1. Using the same skincare products as family members (√ó)

¬†

Although family members may have similar skin types, due to differences in age and lifestyle, everyone's skin condition is different. The toner and lotion used by older family members generally have higher nutritional content. If younger children mix and use them, it can easily lead to acne~

¬†

2. Spraying hydrating mist multiple times a day (√ó)

¬†

If you spray hydrating mist multiple times a day, once the moisture evaporates from the skin surface, it can actually trap the skin in a vicious cycle of repeated dryness and wetness, eventually leading to increasingly dry skin!!

¬†

3. Using more than six skincare products daily (√ó)

¬†

Masks, toners, lotions, creams, essences... If these daily skincare products reach six or more, it can actually increase the burden on the skin. We usually only need basic care, and there's no need to over-indulge our faces.

¬†

4. Using face masks more than five times a week (√ó)

¬†

Generally, using face masks 2-4 times a week is sufficient, especially for cleansing masks. Overuse can damage the skin's stratum corneum.

¬†

5. Applying a thick layer of face cream

¬†

The principle of face cream is to form an oil film on the skin surface to prevent moisture from evaporating. If you already have oily, acne-prone skin and you always apply a thick layer of face cream, you are likely to develop clogged pores.

content:
Note Title: Why Are Women More Likely to Experience Sexual Harassment? (Part 1)
    Note Content: It is said that many women have experienced sexual harassment, whether walking on the street, in the office, or even at home. This unfortunate experience not only makes women feel scared and helpless but also raises questions: Why are women often more susceptible to sexual harassment? Is it because of their overwhelming charm, or is it due to the inevitable barbaric nature of men? Today, let's delve into this issue and explore why women are often more likely to become victims of sexual harassment.

Women are often more noticeable than men. In social settings, women tend to attract more attention than men because they usually wear more eye-catching clothing, have more refined makeup, and exhibit more graceful manners. This concentration of attention not only makes women feel proud and confident but can also lead to fantasies and indecent behavior from men with psychological issues.

Women are often more meticulous and sensitive than men. Their emotional and delicate nature makes them more adept at perceiving others' intentions and emotional changes. This also means that women are more likely to recognize when they are being sexually harassed, as they are better at catching different hints and language, and more easily notice the inappropriate actions of harassers.

Women are often more delicate and vulnerable than men. This vulnerable state makes women easier targets for sexual harassers, who believe that women are incapable of protecting themselves and are more easily threatened and intimidated. This mindset often leads harassers to think they can act with impunity, without considering the victim's feelings and rights.

There are many reasons why women experience sexual harassment, but the end result is always unacceptable. We need to pay more attention to this issue and strive to secure legal rights and protection for victims. At the same time, we need to educate men to understand that sexual harassment is unacceptable behavior and work towards creating a more respectful social environment for women.

[Flying Kiss R][Flying Kiss R][Flying Kiss R]

Yuequan Yanxuan (strictly selected by a dermatologist)‚Äôs boyfriend tranexamic acid essence is very mild. I checked its registration, all green, with no risky ingredients. But don't overuse it, as the concentration is quite high, I only use one-third of a dropper each time.
[Flying Kiss R][Flying Kiss R][Flying Kiss R]
And this mask, which I've mentioned many times, is also from the boyfriend tranexamic acid series, and I've been using it for years.
[Flying Kiss R][Flying Kiss R][Flying Kiss R]

[Flying Kiss R][Flying Kiss R][Flying Kiss R]

[Flying Kiss R][Flying Kiss R][Flying Kiss R]

content:
Note Title: The Friend Who Doesn't Pay Back
    Note Content: There is a friend, or rather an online friend, I suppose. At first, we got along quite well, even talked about meeting up and hanging out. Later, things got delayed due to various reasons. We also had a fight in between and were prepared to cut ties, but then they started reaching out to me actively again, even calling me in the middle of the night. One night, they suddenly asked to borrow money. I said I didn‚Äôt have any because I hadn‚Äôt been working and was relying on my family for money. They asked to use my credit service ‚ÄúHuabei,‚Äù so I lent them 2000 yuan through that, with the promise that they would repay me before the repayment date. However, I forgot about it, and Alipay reminded me that the payment was overdue. I called them, and they sent me 1000 yuan to cover part of it first. After that, they borrowed money from me a couple more times. I didn‚Äôt want to argue much, so I lent them the money, just two or three times. I felt like if I didn‚Äôt lend, they would manipulate me emotionally. Slowly, we started talking less because whenever they called, it was always about them not having money for food and asking me for money. One time, I exploded. They asked me for 500 yuan, and I said I didn‚Äôt have it. They still claimed they hadn‚Äôt eaten for days. At that moment, I told them, 'Don‚Äôt always bring up money every time you call me. If you ask me for money, I don‚Äôt even have enough for myself. My salary is less than 1300, barely enough for myself. My mom is helping my sister look after her kids, and my salary is used to support both me and my mom. We usually don‚Äôt take my sister‚Äôs money because I feel it‚Äôs hard for her too, as she works and has two kids.' Later, they got mad, and we stopped talking. It‚Äôs so frustrating that our chats always turned into monetary demands. I‚Äôm not wealthy either. I asked for my money back a few times, but they always cried poverty, claiming they hadn‚Äôt eaten for days or said they didn‚Äôt have money and were ready to 'lose their life.' It‚Äôs been a year, and they haven‚Äôt mentioned repayment. Yesterday, I messaged them, saying, 'Please pay me back if you have the money; I need it for the HPV vaccine.' They didn‚Äôt reply, but posted something on their social media at night. Originally, I didn‚Äôt plan to push for repayment anymore, but when I think about how much effort and overtime (which is unpaid) I had to go through to make that 1000 yuan, I feel so heartbroken. I almost never leave work on time. This is definitely a case of 'you can never wake someone pretending to be asleep.'

content:
Note Title: A Trip to Yangzhou Without Queuing for Morning Tea
    Note Content: It's the second day in Yangzhou. Although the plan is slightly different from what was made before the trip, by adjusting the schedule for sightseeing and dining times, the experience has gotten better.
	
‚úèDAY ONE
Arrived at the hotel in the afternoon and immediately went to Ge Yuan. Since it was late, there weren't too many people, making it a great spot for taking photos.
When leaving Ge Yuan, the staff was preparing to lock the gates. Then, I walked through Dongguan Street, Caiyi Street, and Dadongmen Street, buying Yangzhou University yogurt with jasmine and cherry blossom flavors at a Love Milk Bar. After that, I reached Yiyuan, where I didn‚Äôt even have to queue!!! Even more luckily, the seat given was next to the window with a view of Siwang Pavilion!!!
‚úèDAY TWO
        Went out at 7:30 a.m., not for morning tea, but to He Yuan first. When I arrived, apart from a few elder visitors, there were almost no others in the garden. The sightseeing experience was excellent.
         Around 9 a.m., I exited and, out of convenience, went for morning tea at Jiulu Fen Zuo near He Yuan. Again, no need to queue. My parents were quite satisfied and even requested to go again tomorrow morning, which I refused due to the inconvenience on the route.
       Initially planned to head to Xiaopangu next, but following Gaode Maps led to the wrong path, so I didn‚Äôt continue searching. Took a cab to Erfen Mingyuelou, and then went to Pishi Street. Reached Quyuan at around 11:40 a.m., where 43 tables were ahead of me in line. After waiting nearly two hours, I was finally seated at 1:30 p.m. For lunch, I could still have oil cake and Wuding buns. It felt like there‚Äôs really no need to queue so early for morning tea.
        I chose to visit Slender West Lake in the afternoon, as I wanted to see the scenery during sunset when most visitors had already left, capturing photos of Wuting Bridge, White Pagoda, and Diaoyutai. Everything was perfect except for the extremely windy conditions today and the noticeable drop in temperature in the evening.
     When leaving at 6:30 p.m., I resolved dinner at Liu Sheji Noodle House, recommended by netizens. It was great and, again, no need to queue.

Note Title: Beauty Back StrategyÔΩúOne Inch Thinner Back, Beautiful Shield‚ùóÔ∏è
    Note Content: Beginner Gym Plan Super suitable golden back exercises for girls~
Those who don't know how to arrange their gym routine, look hereüëá
	
To achieve a beautiful back, you need to pay attention to these:
   Many friends in fitness training prefer to train their chest and neglect the muscle training of their back. In fact, back muscle training is also very important. Daily desk work and forward bending actions lead to most people having a rounded shoulder and hunched back posture. Therefore, fitness beginners need to improve their back posture first[Blow Kiss R][Blow Kiss R]
However, back muscle training exercises are difficult to master, so incorrect back training movements are quite common in the gym. Below are the most common mistakes in back training‚ö†Ô∏è
	
1Ô∏è‚É£Overarching the back during pulldowns
     Many fitness enthusiasts tend to lean back completely when performing back pulldowns, or the target muscles are not accurately engaged, and many people lean back to lift heavier weights to save effort, which is not standardized[Disappointed R][Disappointed R]. When the body leans back too much during latissimus dorsi training, the weight is shifted to the waist, reducing the effort of the latissimus dorsi, and the training effect is significantly diminished. It is recommended to reduce the weight of the back pulldown[Thumbs Up R], allowing the weight to be concentrated on the back, focusing on the trajectory of the elbow movement, with the body slightly leaning back about 10 degrees. Throughout the movement, focus your mind on the latissimus dorsi!
	
2Ô∏è‚É£Overusing bicep strength
     All back training exercises inevitably require the participation of the biceps, but excessive bending of the arms during back exercises will cause the biceps to take over the effort from the back muscles. Why does this happen? Just like the previous mistake, being too greedy[Facepalm R]. When the back muscles are not strong enough to lift heavier weights, one will involuntarily use bicep strength.

#FloatingBed[topic]##Customized[topic]##NoHeadboard[topic]##IronBed[topic]##BedFrame[topic]#
1 Load-bearing: The new floating iron bed overall bed frame is fully made of steel, very sturdy, and has a load-bearing capacity of over 1.5 tons
2 Noise: The squeaky noises that occur with prolonged use of beds are caused by unreasonable structures and insufficient materials in some traditional iron beds. We have already resolved this issue. The entire bed frame features a welded structure, effectively preventing noise caused by friction at the connections between components; additionally, specially made fittings provide added stability and fixedness.
3 Surface Treatment: The bed frame surface is treated using powder electrostatic spraying technology, making it rust-resistant, chip-resistant, eco-friendly, durable, odorless, and ready to use upon purchase. Powder coating involves using powder coating equipment (electrostatic spray guns) to spray the powder coating material onto the surface of the object. Under the effect of static electricity, the powder adheres evenly to the surface, forming a powdered coating. This powdered coating is then baked at high temperatures to flatten and solidify, resulting in final coatings with varying effects depending on the type of powder; powder coating has superior strength, adhesion, corrosion resistance, and aging resistance compared to traditional paints, albeit at higher costs.
4 Installation: The bed frame is very easy to assemble, requiring only a few feet to be attached and screws to be tightened. The necessary installation tools are well-equipped, making it a task that can be independently completed by a female.
5 Usage: This floating bed frame is dual-purpose; it can be used directly on the floor or fixed to the headboard or wall. The headboard position has four pre-drilled connection holes. You can purchase expansion screws and hire a renovator for installation or buy specialized connecting brackets in-store for installation.
6 Ambient Lighting: Ambient light strips can be installed. The strips come with self-adhesive backing, which securely attaches to the bed frame without needing any drilling, allowing for immediate use.

Note Title: No.5 "Toad Went to See the Psychotherapist" Check-in üå†
    Note Content: [SweatingR] The first book of May, this book had been sitting in my Kindle for almost a year without being read. I saw many people recommend it while many others criticized it üëé. However, I personally think this book is amazing üéüÔ∏è
[SweatingR][SweatingR] First of all, I think this book is suitable for people who are experiencing certain "emotional illnesses" (depression, anxiety, etc.) üìñ. Please don't argue for the sake of arguing, thanks.
[SweatingR][SweatingR][SweatingR] The book records Toad's experience with depression and his journey through ten psychotherapy sessions. The text is simple and easy to understand.
[PlantR] The biggest takeaway after reading is that having an emotional illness is not shameful, let alone terrifying. Through Toad's ten interviews, you can clearly understand how to define depression and how to face your "irrational" behaviors and attitudes.
[PlantR] Secondly, reading such books indeed has a calming function for one's emotions.
[PlantR] Lastly, whether or not you have read this book, whether you are in the parent mode, adult mode, or child mode, please make sure to face your current predicament and save yourself in time. After all, there are so many wonderful things waiting for you.
[AtmosphereR][AtmosphereR][AtmosphereR][AtmosphereR] Below are the parts I liked, sharing [AtmosphereR][AtmosphereR][AtmosphereR][AtmosphereR]
1‚É£Ô∏è Sometimes, when friends or partners around you are quite excellent, the other side might feel troubled or inferior. Even well-meaning reminders or help might make the weaker side feel uncomfortable. The stronger side should appropriately show kindness and vulnerability, avoid being dominant in everything, and give the other person a sense of presence.
2‚É£Ô∏è True friends must extend a helping hand in difficult times, whether or not the person in question is willing.
3‚É£Ô∏è Be clear about what you want to do. No matter what you do to please others, the things you must complete can only be done by yourself.
4‚É£Ô∏è Actually, every day should have expectations because each day is full of exciting new possibilities.
5‚É£Ô∏è Improvements in a person's inner world seem to be reflected in gradually recovering social life.
6‚É£Ô∏è Anger can effectively combat depression. Angry people don't feel guilt because they are always blaming others. Their way of self-defense is to project their internal fears onto others, thereby redirecting their internal rage outward.
7‚É£Ô∏è In this state, we can plan, consider, act, and decide. We can behave rationally and reasonably. In this state, all the knowledge and skills we possess serve us without being driven by the past voices of our parents or entangled by childhood emotions. Instead, we can think about the current situation and decide what to do based on facts.
8‚É£Ô∏è May you always have the ability to give and receive love.
9‚É£Ô∏è No criticism is stronger than self-criticism, and no judge is harsher than ourselves. #BookList[Topic] #ToadWenttoSeePsychotherapist[Topic] #ReadingNotesCheckin[Topic] #May[Topic] #Depression[Topic] #Psychology[Topic]#

content:
Note Title: "About Teacher Boyuan Picking Up My Phone"
    Note Content: Very crazy, I'll put the signing repo aside and talk about this incredibly coincidental event. On Friday evening at T3 waiting lounge, I brushed past a Myriad video about them, so they should have already taken off. At that time, I regretted not catching a glimpse of the lead in this shared space, thinking we were on the same flight. I was on the last flight of the day to Xiamen, and true to Shandong Airlines' reputation, the plane accelerated onto the runway and immediately took off üõ´. My previous seat was far back in the economy cabin, and before boarding, I could upgrade. Not willing to spend for business, I upgraded to super economy (just behind business class). I have two phones, an iPhone and a Samsung. Since no one was beside me, I placed the Samsung on the adjacent seat while using the iPhone to record the outside view. When descending into Xiamen, I heard a "thump" and realized something fell. I turned to look and noticed a piece of wet tissue on the seat, and it had dropped directly below the front seat, so I assumed my phone must be in about the same spot. I used a flashlight to search but couldn't find it, starting to panic‚Äîoh no, I hadn't filmed anything; could the phone be already gone?! Pleading with the gentleman in front and alerting flight attendants, they all started helping me search. After a long time searching in the economy cabin and failing, an attendant went to the business class section and found it after a while. After verifying through fingerprint unlock, the phone was returned to me. Thinking it was just a small episode, I waited for my luggage, too sleepy to open my eyes, when I suddenly heard someone call "Boyuan." I turned to look but saw no one. Since there was only one luggage carousel from Beijing to Xiamen, I guessed Boyuan might have been on the same flight as me. I planned to ask during the signing and had the following conversation:
"Boyuan, did you fly from Beijing to Xiamen yesterday?" (testing)
"Yes" (confused)
"Was it Shandong Airlines?"
"Yes" (puzzled)
"Were you in the business class?"
"Yes"
"Do you know a phone slid into business class?!" (getting excited)
"Yes"
"That was my phone!"
"Oh, that was your phone? I picked it up from under my seat." (laughing)
"What?!" (shocked)
(Then Boyuan lowered his head to sign while I was still too excited, forgetting the special signature my sponsor needed.)
"Boyuan, could you look at the camera, please? The person raising a hand." (asked a sister in the back to record with my Samsung)
Boyuan saw, posed for a bit, looked at me, and said, "So this is the phone you lost?" (laughing)
"You even remember this [laughing tears R]"
Before I could explain my sponsor's needs, I was pushed away by gzry (their hand was basically glued to my back, forcing me forward. No one could say more than a few words before being pushed away!!!).
Later when I came to my senses, I saw the signature Boyuan gave me. Me: .. Sponsor boss, rest assured! Leave it to me! I'm definitely going to mess it up! (Later, managing to scramble and get a generic blessings signature from a fellow fan, the sponsor kindly agreed.)
Boyuan, rest assured, I will treasure this signature forever [crying R]

content:
Note Title: I'm starting a business!
    Note Content: A lazy girl wasted 8 months and is now starting a business!
Are there any sisters born in the year of the Rooster? Personally, I feel that those born in the year of the Rooster are naturally hardworking, and once they are determined, they take on everything diligently and responsibly. In the 8 months after quitting my job, I completely lay flat. Although I don't have the pressure of mortgages or car loans, my personality made me really anxious. This year, I finally decided to take a step forward and come to Guangzhou to visit my family. Although my parents are understanding and don‚Äôt push me to find a job, I still feel extremely anxious and confused. What kind of job should I look for? What small business should I start? Where should I begin? Yesterday, I went to Guangzhou's accessories market to get some goods, and when I opened Little Red Book, I saw an article advising against starting a business selling accessories. Reading that made my heart race. But the reason I want to post this diary entry today is to express my inner thoughts: Life offers many choices. If you don‚Äôt take that first step, you are likely to remain confused and stagnant. A small-scale business, once successful, can encourage us to move forward courageously. Even if, by chance, things don‚Äôt go as planned, we had so many entrepreneurial ideas before and at least we gave it a try. Experimentation leads to knowledge. The discouraging articles are not necessarily unreliable‚Äîthey can serve as references to help us think clearly about how to proceed and refine our plans. Alright, enough said. Is there a stranger who can send me a word of encouragement? üò≠

    Note Content: #Beautiful Scenery on the Journey[Topic]# 
‚ù§Ô∏èThe first stop in Italy was the Milan Cathedral, it was truly breathtaking, so beautiful it didn't seem real. Wearing a 100-meter long skirt made for great photos
üìçMilan Cathedral - Duomo di Milano
P.za del Duomo, 20122 Milano MI, Italy
üé´I bought a combo ticket in advance on the official website, allowing direct entry‚úÖ
üï∏Ô∏èOfficial Website: duomomilano.it

üì∑Photography: Sharing photography spots 
üîÖp2-p3 is the exterior of the Milan Cathedral, you can buy a fridge magnet to take a photo together, you can shoot upwards to avoid the crowd 
üîÖp4 be careful, a black man kept putting grains in my hand, I was confused and took it, the pigeons ate it very enthusiastically, it scared me to death, hence this photo. Then he asked us for money, we realized we were scammed and didn't give him anything, we really didn't have cash and left quickly. Friends, be careful

    Note Content: In early March, a very small number of Hainan lychees hit the market, with prices remaining high due to scarcity, roughly around 40-50 yuan per jin. About a month later, the March Red variety from Haikou and other areas will mature, followed by a large influx of Feizixiao and White Sugar Jar lychees from the northwestern part of Hainan. Then comes the peak season in May-June, with the largest quantities from major producing areas like Guangxi and Guangdong, including varieties like March Red, Feizixiao, White Sugar Jar, Glutinous Rice Lychee, and Guiwei. During this peak period, lychee prices will see a significant drop. As a seasonal short shelf-life product, lychee prices fluctuate wildly every year.
It's worth mentioning that this year is basically confirmed to be a bumper year, with lychee flowering rates in Hainan and the Guangdong-Guangxi regions exceeding 90%. If there are no extreme weather conditions in the producing areas, domestic lychee production will experience a bumper harvest. content:
Note Title: Inlay Makes Jadeite More Beautiful
    Note Content: Today, let's talk about my personal views on jadeite inlay. A friend asked me, is it better to buy jadeite that is already inlaid, or to buy a bare stone and inlay it yourself? I think for beginners, it's better to buy the inlaid one, what you see is what you get. If you know a little more, you can consider buying a bare stone and inlaying it yourself, pursuing personalization while also being more cost-effective.
Inlay is a magical thing. Good full-cut diamonds can add light to the main stone, good inlay techniques can adjust the water of the main stone, and reasonable backing can make the color of the main stone more beautiful. Generally, inlay is like beauty treatment, good inlay is like plastic surgery.
There are also theories that unbacked jadeite is better than backed jadeite, but I don't agree with this view. The purpose of inlay is to make jadeite more beautiful. If a stone is suitable for backed inlay, even if its quality is very good, I would still back it. Beauty comes first. When buying jewelry, we pursue the wearing effect, not to show off that my stone is good, my stone is good, unbacked, unbacked. [doge]

content:
Note Title: Non-equipment enthusiast discusses how to choose a 5Xmm standard lens
    Note Content: Actually, I have more 5Xmm lenses in my hands than these, but these are more distinctive. I believe a standard lens doesn't necessarily have to be exactly 50mm. Anything in the 5Xmm range counts in my opinion. If you disagree, you must be right.
	

While sorting through my collection, I realized that I don‚Äôt have lenses with high optical quality and not overly stylized, like the ART series, GM series, etc. This must be due to poverty. There‚Äôs a saying, "No weak fighters among standard lenses," which roughly means every brand's 5Xmm lenses are competitive. My experience supports this, so I‚Äôll describe the reasons for purchasing and my thoughts on each lens briefly.
	

From left to right: helios77-4 50mm f1.8 and Voigtlander 58mm f1.4. Because all the Eight Elements lenses I had were in poor condition, I wanted a lens with a Soviet style and decent mechanical state, so I bought this Helios. As for the Voigtlander, I got it to pair with my TPK6-16Z as the main lens because of its high contrast. The actual tests were indeed great, and the 58mm main lens on the TPK just perfectly covers full-frame. Both can work perfectly for 4433.
	

Takumar 55mm f1.8: I picked this up in an old lens auction group. At that time, I was collecting Takumar lenses, so I bid 100 yuan and got it after one raise. This one is generally very low-priced, and its overall quality is similar to the "Plastic Fantastic," but with more stylized bokeh. The tactile feel is far superior to other budget standard lenses. If you don‚Äôt own a standard lens and want to try one, I highly recommend the Takumar 55mm.
	

Canon 50L: I was out shooting with someone who had a 50L. I asked if I could mount it to feel the f1.2, and he said no. On my way home, I bought a new one. Its weakness is its strength: soft and dreamy. Close-up shots might be too soft, but at around 1m, it becomes acceptable. Great for portrait photography but not other tasks. (I‚Äôll write about this lens separately later.)
	

Hasselblad C50: It‚Äôs roughly equivalent to a 28mm f2 when used with a Hasselblad body. It‚Äôs actually a wide-angle lens, with poor performance against backlighting but very smooth in low light. It can be adapted for full-frame, though the aperture is relatively small.
	

Mamiya 55mm f2.8: Considered a wide-angle on a 645 body, and delivers very beautiful, soft, and smooth bokeh when adapted to full-frame with a speed booster. Super cheap.
	

Dulens58mm f2: Emmmmm, I‚Äôll write about this separately; it‚Äôs a highly controversial brand.
	

SIRUI 50mm f2.8 1.6x anamorphic widescreen: This lens has been heavily critiqued. Its characteristic is sharpness, which ironically is the least needed feature for a stylized lens. (I‚Äôll write about this one separately later.)
	

Ending abruptly because of a lack of characters, the 5Xmm focal length is a very commonly used one. I often complete a set of photos or even shoot an entire short film using just one lens. From a styling perspective, I think of this lens as a basic undershirt, which is why I own quite a few 5Xmm lenses. Actually, every single one is great, and I choose a different one each time I go out. But I don‚Äôt recommend buying so many‚Äîjust one "scientific" and one "mystical" lens would be sufficiently versatile.

Note Title: How is the Zibo College Entrance Exam Retake Institution? A Brand New Start
    Note Content: Retaking is a new chapter different from the preparation for the senior three exams. We need to abandon the past experiences of the college entrance exam and senior three, and welcome the upcoming college entrance exam again with a brand new attitude. In the Zibo College Entrance Exam Retake Institution, retakers need to start learning anew, facing stricter management discipline, and preparing for the next college entrance exam. Retaking is both a rechallenge and a new challenge for retakers, who must muster the courage to face the familiar yet unfamiliar challenge of the college entrance exam.


How do retakers begin to welcome the learning life of retaking in the Zibo College Entrance Exam Retake Institution? When retakers enroll in Lixing School, they are arranged for an entrance test, and classes are divided based on their college entrance exam scores and entrance test scores, with a small class system. Supervising teachers will develop a one-on-one personal study plan for you, and the homeroom teacher will set up a personal file system for real-time updates, identifying and solving problems promptly, teaching students according to their aptitude, finding the characteristics of retakers, and being even stricter after class, punishing every slightest mistake severely.


The learning life of retaking is much stricter than that of senior three. The school's management system is stricter, with a fully enclosed boarding mode, strictly prohibiting retakers from leaving the school gate, requiring attendance checks for classes, ensuring retakers' attendance, and homeroom teachers following classes to maintain discipline. During school hours, carrying mobile phones or other disciplinary items is strictly prohibited, and the punishment is quite severe if discovered. Moreover, the school unifies the daily routine of retakers and strictly implements morning and evening self-study, with homeroom teachers responsible for the management and supervision of the daily routine.


It doesn't matter if the college entrance exam results are not good. Coming to the Zibo College Entrance Exam Retake Institution is a new beginning. content:
Note Title: Images from Shanghai Art Fair 2023
    Note Content: This year, it's still held at the Shanghai Exhibition Center. However, parking is not available, so I parked in the nearby residential area across the street for 10 yuan per hour.
Tickets cost 120 yuan. Some people bought fake tickets at the entrance in an attempt to save money, so be careful. Entering through the West Hall, there were many foreigners here, all very stylishly dressed.
The entrance featured the Family-themed exhibition.
Mexican works with unique highlights from different perspectives.
Spanish works in the "inbreeding series" that are hard to understand.
American black artworks with seemingly no cultural undertone.
Moving further in, there were the "Garden of Earthly Delights" series by European artists from Bohemia. Its decadent style and controversial themes stood out. By the pillar nearby, you could scan a code to receive postcards.
As we walked through the corridor, I saw a clay sculpture. Do you know what the artist was trying to say with it?
Before entering the main hall, we passed the Shanghai-themed exhibition, which perfectly highlighted several iconic spots in Shanghai. Shot during dusk and under night lights, they looked absolutely stunning.
When we arrived at the main hall, today's highlight remained the colorful Porsche 911. The heavy investment made it incredibly flashy.
Finally, we reached the grand plaza. Like a trade fair, each gallery had its own unique features. Every photo tells a story.
There were so many brilliant works. It's truly worth spending a whole day to appreciate them thoroughly.

Note Title: Quanzhou‚Äî‚ÄîHalf City of Lights, Half City of Immortals
    Note Content: The scorching weather makes the weekend without overtime even more boring. Looking at the high-speed train, it's only 50 minutes away, so I decided to embark on a spontaneous trip.
[PlaneR] Itinerary: Kaiyuan Temple‚Äî‚ÄîWest Street‚Äî‚ÄîXiao Xicheng‚Äî‚ÄîClock Tower‚Äî‚ÄîQuanzhou Cinema (Quanzhou Big Red Characters)‚Äî‚ÄîWeiyuan Tower‚Äî‚ÄîZhongshan Road‚Äî‚ÄîChengtian Temple‚Äî‚ÄîConfucius Temple‚Äî‚ÄîQingjing Mosque‚Äî‚ÄîGuan Yue Temple
[StarR] The twin towers of Kaiyuan Temple are truly exquisite, entirely made of stone, even the plaques are carved from stone.
[StarR] West Street is too crowded, filled with all kinds of delicious food. You can take photos of the stone towers in the alley opposite Kaiyuan Temple, or on the third floor of the tourist center.
[StarR] The arcade buildings on Zhongshan Road are full of South Asian style, telling stories from that era.
[StarR] The Confucius Temple is a row of Minnan-style large houses. Not far from the Zhuzi Bridge is the modest Qingjing Mosque, a typical Islamic architectural style. Next to the Qingjing Mosque is the bustling Tonghuai Guan Yue Temple, plus the nearby Christian church on Zhongshan Road. With so many deities gathered, will they really not fight[FullMoonR]
[StarR] I ate vinegar meat, which I always thought was vegetarian meat, so sour...

    Note Content: How tough 2022 and 2023 have been! Just look at the friends around me searching for jobs!
	
Last year, a sister and her husband, both in the same industry, faced massive layoffs and became unemployed one after the other
	
Her husband took a pay cut to join a startup company a month later, and she, reminded by a friend, remembered to apply for unemployment insurance

I hope her experience can help more unemployed sisters see this and apply earlier to reduce anxiety.

content:
Note Title: Experience Sharing of Rooftop Tent UsageÔΩúADA Wilderness Hunter
    Note Content: I'd like to share my experience using a rooftop tent, including some pros and cons for your reference, to help you decide if a rooftop tent is suitable for you.
I am an avid self-driving camper, and I chose a rooftop tent because it allows me to set off at any time. My rooftop tent is the ADA Wilderness Hunter, which I have used for over a year. Here are the pros and cons of this rooftop tent.
Pros ‚úîÔ∏è:
1‚É£ Portability: You can camp and rest anytime, anywhere. With some practice, it takes only ten minutes to set up and pack up. Any place you like can become your campsite, whether by a stream, lake, mountain top, or desert, as long as your car can reach it.
2‚É£ Comfort: The ADA Wilderness Hunter tent comes with a memory foam mattress, which is extremely comfortable. The space inside the rooftop tent is also very large, easily accommodating a family of three. At 184cm tall, I find the space inside the tent ample, making it convenient to change clothes.
3‚É£ Safety: Most rooftop tents are installed on the car roof, while pickups may choose to install them on the back. Rooftop tents solve the problem of damp ground and small animals during camping. This tent also has a mesh to keep out mosquitoes and sand.
4‚É£ There are some features of this tent that I really like: 1, the rooftop tent has a skylight, allowing you to lie in the tent and stargaze. 2, the tent's waterproofing is excellent, made of 600D Oxford cloth. Once during a camping trip, it rained heavily at night, and the next morning, I checked the entire tent and found no water inside. 3, the tent comes with an LED light strip that can be used by plugging in a power bank. 4, all the zippers on this tent use SBS zippers, which are very smooth. I think these small details are very well done.
Cons ‚ùå:
1‚É£ This rooftop tent does not have a thermal inner liner. In winter, when camping in sub-zero temperatures, I use a wood stove and an electric blanket to solve the insulation problem. Most of my camping is done with a sub-zero temperature sleeping bag, which is also very comfortable and not cold. The tent's sealing is excellent, and there are also ventilation holes on the top and sides.
2‚É£ A layer of condensation can form on the inner wall of the tent when there is a significant temperature difference between inside and outside. This seems to be a common issue with rooftop tents, mainly due to the water vapor evaporated from the body and exhaled during sleep, forming under the temperature difference. Just wipe it down before packing up the next morning.
3‚É£ Since accessing the rooftop tent requires a ladder, it can be a bit inconvenient to go to the toilet at night. I usually relieve myself before entering the tent.
The above is my genuine experience using a rooftop tent. If there are any inaccuracies in my personal feelings, please forgive me.
PS: Honestly, rooftop tents are not cheap, ranging from 5000 to 20000 yuan in the market. Using a rooftop tent with your car is very convenient, but I suggest you consider your usage scenarios and frequency. If you are like me, an avid self-driving camper, I highly recommend you get one.

The output of rice and grain is very abundant, and the Jianchuan Prefecture all come here to obtain sufficient supplies...

Note Title: A Brief Talk on Disney Parent-Child Trip
    Note Content: I am the type who economizes on spending. I bought a 33 VIP pass for myself, a regular ticket for my husband, and since my child is under 3 years old, she did not require a ticket and followed me throughout the trip.
The child woke up naturally, and we entered the park at 9 am. We used the 33 VIP lane, so no need to queue. My husband entered through the main entrance an hour earlier, played two attractions, and waited for us inside.
We played from left to right. I played the speed ride myself, while my husband took the child to play either Woody or Slinky Dog. These two attractions had a 20-minute queue around 9 am.
The guide insisted we play Buzz Lightyear; this attraction always has a 5-10 minute wait, so no rush. I skipped the guide and went on my own.
I reunited with my husband and child, took the child to play Peter Pan's Flight and Winnie the Pooh. Since we had fast passes, the wait was around 10 minutes for both.
Then, we went to the Honey Pot in front of Winnie; the queue was also about 20 minutes. My husband and I divided and queued separately, so the child played once with my husband and then once with me, which made her quite happy.
Next, we went to the dwarf ride, which had the longest queue in the park. But it was okay since we had a fast pass; it was only a 10-minute wait. The height requirement was 97 cm, but our child is only 95 cm. We deliberately had her wear dad shoes, which added about 2.2 cm. There are two height checks, and we just barely met the requirement.
At noon, we had an appointment for photos. After the photos, we went for lunch.
After lunch, we played Pirates of the Caribbean. It was dark inside, and the child fell asleep‚Äîjust the perfect time for her nap. I took the opportunity to play Horizons and Thunder Mountain.
By 3 pm, we had finished almost all the attractions. Afterward, we just enjoyed watching the parade and took it easy.
My husband and I had played these attractions before, so they didn't hold much interest for us anymore in terms of the attractions themselves‚Äîthey're not as good as Universal Studios. This time, it was mainly for the child, and the overall experience was still very good.
